	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, here's what I've learned about factions so far.<br><br>Factions can be maxed, no doubt about that.<br><br>To continue raising other associated factions once a given faction is maxed or bottomed out, you must be killed by the NPC you are killing to raise factions.<br><br>When doing quest's to increase factions and you max that faction, you must be killed by something that gives positive faction for the group that is maxed.  In the case of the neriak red wine quest, your screwed because no NPC i've ever seen or heard of give positive darkbargainer's faction.<br><br>As of the last patch, all faction issues **seem** to have cleared up, as far as maxed faction groups go.  Once a faction is maxed, however, you won't know about it.  If a given group can be brought up above the level it is when it's maxed by dying to an opposing factioned NPC, then you will have to get yourself killed periodically to ensure that you can continue raising it.<br><br>Your faction goes down faster than it goes up.  I think most everyone knows about this.<br><br>Not all quest's increase faction equally.  In the case of one of the people above, he was able to increase his faction faster by turning in just a few gnoll fangs.  In my case, I gave about 6 backpack's full of bandages to that little halfling in misty thicket, which got me from dubious to amiable.  This also depends on how the faction works with a given group.  In Qeynos, it may be that both forms of KOS are way deep, whereas amiable, etc are just above base, and it may take a very short time overall for uncorrupt qeynos people to like you.<br><br>A possible theory I have though, is on whether or not faction increases faster the higher you are.  For instance, when your kos, if you do something to raise faction it only gives you say, 1 point.  If your dubious maybe it gives you 2.  Then at indifferent still 2, but when you get into more friendly factions, you gain it at an increasingly faster rate.<br><br>-Desbarolis -- 39th bard<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
