<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=97147439812884></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97147439812884><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/facstrat.html?forum=3&mid=97147439812884 style='color: darkblue;'>Impossible to Raise</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=1888><span id=>PhreakyPhreaks</span></a><br><span id=notbold>65 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Oct 13th 5:59 PM</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.63]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>As a Dark Elf I know that if your faction with a race is dubiousor below when you create your character then you can NEVER raise it above that. Your faction will simply cap. I was hunting orcs when I was young in EC and my faction kept going up and then it stopped. I assumed I had good faction but when I conned a guard it was dubious. I can never raise above that, but I dont mind as long as I can go on the boat without fear of guards =) And btw merchants will not sell to you if you are dubious or below which sucks but its alright. Hope that helps some stuff. In other words, DE's Trolls and Ogres can never go up beyond dubious with any other race<br><br>Peace<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
