<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9714629087295></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9714629087295><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/facstrat.html?forum=3&mid=9714629087295 style='color: darkblue;'>Questsions</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=1><span id=Administrator>Illia</span></a>, <span id=Administrator>Administrator</span><br><span id=notbold>35 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Oct 13th 2:48 PM</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.65]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The main questions I wonder about are:<br><br><LI>Are there caps on faction, or is it possible (assuming you can find the appropriate kills or quests) for anyone to reach any standing with any faction<br><br><LI><i>If</i> there are caps on faction modifiers, can they be hit by <b>any</b> appropriate deed.  In other words, will completing a given quest say 10,000 times bring you to the cap ?  or could a given quest only take you to part of the modifier, and then you'd need to find a new modifier?<br><br><LI>Are negative faction modifiers permanent?  By this I mean that are negative modifiers tracked separately than positive, and that when you are ping-ponging a faction (lowering, then raising - say with treants) you're still accumulating the negative faction, just offsetting it.<br><br>Just a few things to think about :)<br>&nbsp;<br>--Illia</td></tr>
